Reasoning: 
1. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the problem of regulating the ratio of two cell populations using external control inputs. The authors present three control strategies to achieve this, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Systems and Control sub-category. 
2. cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper mentions physical and technological constraints occurring in experimental microfluidic platforms, which suggests that it may also belong to the Mechanical Engineering sub-category. 
3. q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods): The paper uses stochastic agent-based simulations to validate the designed controllers, which suggests that it may also belong to the Quantitative Methods sub-category. 
4. q-bio.TO (Tissues and Organs): The paper deals with regulating the ratio of two cell populations, which may be relevant to the Tissues and Organs sub-category. 
5. q-bio.SC (Subcellular Processes): The paper mentions a genetic toggle switch as an example of a bistable memory mechanism, which may be relevant to the Subcellular Processes sub-category.
